What you need to know:

Jane Marriott, OBE, the British High Commissioner to Kenya shares her experience of sexual assault and how it impacted her life.She speaks as the British High Commissioner, yes, but mostly as a woman reliving a horrific episode that took place 17 years ago.The backdrop is Iraq, the year 2003, in the world’s post-9-11 war-filled haze and Ms Marriott, 27 then, decided to volunteer her time towards the transition to civilian rule.A man found his way into her room - she can’t remember what he looked like but he was in his late 30s, early 40, physically bigger and stronger than her.